description:
**Job description**

Mediflex Surgical Products is a medical device manufacturer that has been in business for more than 50 years. We are looking to fill the role of Assembler/Shipper in our production department. This person will be tasked with picking of components, basic mechanical assembling of medical devices, labelling and packaging. Additionally this person will be responsible for assisting in our shipping department by boxing 5-10 orders/day and creating shipping labels for the shipments.

Requirements:

* Able to read and speak English fluently;
* Able to use hand tools such as screw drivers, thread taps, and wrenches;
* Able to use machines such as drill press, grinder, bead blast machine and a 20 ton press;
* Able to follow directions, receive constructive criticism, and avoid conflicts with others;
* Able to work as part of a team.

Skills that are a plus:

* Use of hand tools, and some machines (Drill Press, Grinders,etc.) - Training can be provided;
* Previous shipping experience is a plus.

Additional information:

* Shift is 8:30-4:30 with very minimal OT if necessary;
* Working conditions are those of a clean warehouse;
* Dress code for work is "clean" with the knowledge that you will get dirty (usually presentable t-shirt and jeans);
* Health Insurance and retirement plan available after 6 months of employment (retirement after 12 months);
* 2 weeks vacation available after 1 year of employment;
* Starting wages negotiable and commensurate with experience;
* If you do not have any previous experience you can be considered with a good cover letter on why we should hire you.

Job Type: Full-time

Pay: $17.00 - $19.00 per hour

Benefits:

* Dental insurance
* Flexible spending account
* Health insurance
* Paid time off
* Retirement plan

Schedule:

* 8 hour shift
* Monday to Friday

Work Location: In person
